gs to the Asia region because it tracks the Tokyo Stock Exchange in Japan.\n- \"Up days\" refer to trading days where the closing price is higher than the opening price. \"Down days\" refer to trading days where the closing price is lower than the opening price.\n- The term \"average intraday volatility\" refers to the average relative fluctuation of a stock index within each trading day. It is typically computed as (High - Low) / Open for each day, then averaged across a given time period."
